{"id":3242,"date":"2012-05-20T00:11:12","date_gmt":"2012-05-20T04:11:12","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=3242"},"modified":"2023-03-02T10:32:28","modified_gmt":"2023-03-02T06:32:28","slug":"nothing-greater-tawhid","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/05\/20\/nothing-greater-tawhid\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Tawhid: Nothing greater than to testify Allah is One"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, &#8220;<strong>Moses said: My Lord, teach me something with which I can remember You and call upon You. Allah said: Say &#8216;there is no God but Allah.&#8217; Moses said: My Lord, all of Your servants say this. Allah said: O Moses, if the seven heavens with their inhabitants, as well as the seven earths, were upon a scale against the statement &#8216;there is no God but Allah,&#8217; then &#8216;there is no God but Allah&#8217; would outweigh them.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 6218<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/i>(authentic) according to Ibn Hajar<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u200f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064e\u0649\u200f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u0651 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u0651\u0645\u0652\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0634\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0626\u064b\u0627